Defendant Tramaine Jovon Reed in court with attorney Jeff T. Wilson.  Defendant Tramaine Jovon Reed in custody.  Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared on behalf of Sara Schroeder for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea hearing proceeds.   Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms or body armor.    Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.     

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by:  Ms. Latanya R., defendant's mother.  The Court imposed the following sentence:   The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 6 years.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 3 years with credit for 115 days time served.  Defendant shall serve 3 years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program but not for  the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of his determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. The Court STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation to the State Department of Corrections for a period of four (4) years.
 * Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION (and Extended Supervision, if revoked):
 - No contact with Hollis M. or Dominos Pizza
 - Serve 12 months at the House of Correction, with release to the Day Reporting Center only; good time allowed;
 - No contact with co-actors Darryl Gooden, Dekory Terrell, "Ashley" or "Brittney;"
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Urine screens;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Parenting classes;
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements by the end of probationary period.  Should defendant get revoked and be sent to prison, Court ordered monies taken by the Department of Correction from up to 25% of prison funds.  Balance would be then be paid while on Extended Supervision.   Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

